  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DEC 2 Recovery and Reintegration of Ebola Survivors and EVD Affected Vulnerable Communities NMJD</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation of 4 PHUs in Kenema district including the installation of solar panels
Provide furniture including mattresses for the  4 PHUs
Advocacy campaign to promote quality health service delivery
Institutional training to 20 nonemployed youths including the provision of 3 games and sport activities for vulnerable children
targetting chiefdoms with high EVD cases</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improve health service delivery in EVD affected communities and thereby provide quality health for the communities. Also by providing livelihood means for the youths and community people, there will be an increase in their economic power giving them a higher standard of living - improved nutrition, health care education and other basic necessities can be met. This will improve the communities&apos; resilience and response</narrative>
  </description>
